  "commentary": "With SPX at 6825.12 sitting right between the max negative gamma wall at 6820 (-8014.2M) and max positive gamma at 6840 (+7578.5M), dealers are likely buying the current dip given we're below the flip at 6864 and in PIN regime. The massive GEX surge creates a tight trading range with strong amplifying forces at 6820 (dealers forced to buy) and heavy stabilizing resistance at 6840 (dealers selling), suggesting any move will be sharp but contained within this 20-point corridor. Watch for volatility compression if price holds above 6820, but a break below triggers forced dealer buying that could accelerate the move lower.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action between 6820-6840 with sharp moves at the boundaries.",
